Apply KISS, YAGNI and SOLID principles.
Use pytest for testing.
Generate complete tests for the application.
Search for appropriate libraries and versions on https://pypi.org/.
Use uv for Python dependency management. Note that it uses pyproject.toml and not requirements.txt.
Always install the latest version of each library.
Use "uv add packagename" to add a package, eg uv add openai
Use "uv add --dev packagename" to add a dev package, eg uv add --dev pytest
Install the ruff package for linting and formatting

Read library documention with the firecrawl tool using the following specific URLs and links from those URLs, and then fall back on general search or deep research if required.

